                            <comment id="16844605" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 21 May 2019 07:52:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you double check you see this on latest Camel 2.x version. I think it works on 2.24.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16844991" author="eximius" created="Tue, 21 May 2019 15:55:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, test passes, but it should FAIL &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16845465" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 22 May 2019 03:37:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;set the expected message count = 1 for camel 2.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16845721" author="eximius" created="Wed, 22 May 2019 09:46:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davsclaus&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davsclaus&quot;&gt;davsclaus&lt;/a&gt; - I know about `expected message count`, but don&apos;t you think that `expectedHeaderReceived` should work without it?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see that you changed that for 3.x. Is there any possibility to backport it to 2.x?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16845734" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 22 May 2019 09:59:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not really as we are too busy with Camel 3.x and this is only for testing, not production usage of Camel, and it has been like this for Camel 2.x always.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are doing something very seldom to just assert a single header.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
